: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Guard dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guard_dog\">guard dogs</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Police dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Police_dog\">police dogs</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">.</span><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rottweiler#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup></p>','','full_html'),('node','article',0,30,30,'und',0,'<p><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">El&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">dóberman</strong><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%C3%B3berman#cite_note-7\">7</a></sup><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;es una raza relativamente reciente, debe su nombre al alemán Karl Friedrich Louis Dobermann, quien a finales del&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Siglo XIX\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siglo_XIX\">siglo XIX</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, emprende la tarea de crear una nueva&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Raza de perro\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raza_de_perro\">raza de perro</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;que sirviera eficazmente a su difícil trabajo como&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Recaudador de impuestos\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recaudador_de_impuestos\">recaudador de impuestos</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">. Para conseguir el nacimiento de esta nueva raza, se emplearon cruces de otras razas caninas como el&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Rottweiler\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rottweiler\">Rottweiler</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, el&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Beauceron\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beauceron\">Beauceron</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, el&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Braco de Weimar\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Braco_de_Weimar\">Braco de Weimar</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, el&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Manchester terrier\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester_terrier\">Manchester terrier</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, o el&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Pinscher\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinscher\">Pinscher</a><span style=\"color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">. La principal función de esta raza en sus orígenes, fue la de proteger a su creador frente a potenciales asaltantes interesados en la recaudación de los impuestos que solía portar.</span></p>','','full_html'),('node','article',0,31,31,'und',0,'<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">El&nbsp;<strong>Pastor Australiano</strong>&nbsp;es una raza de&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Perro\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perro\">perro</a>&nbsp;de&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Pastor\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pastor\">pastoreo</a>&nbsp;que se desarrolló en los ranchos en el Oeste de los&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Estados Unidos\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estados_Unidos\">Estados Unidos</a>. A pesar de su nombre, la raza, conocida comúnmente como un australiano \"Aussie\", no se originó en&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Australia\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia\">Australia</a>, se originó en&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"EUA\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/EUA\">EUA</a>. Su nombre oficial es Australian Shepherd.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Adquirieron su nombre por la asociación con pastores vascos que vinieron a los Estados Unidos desde Australia. Los pastores de Australia aumentaron rápidamente su popularidad con el auge del oeste después de la&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Segunda Guerra Mundial\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Segunda_Guerra_Mundial\">Segunda Guerra Mundial</a>. Se hicieron conocidos para el público general a través de los&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Rodeo estadounidense\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rodeo_estadounidense\">rodeos</a>, espectáculos de caballos, y a través de&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Película\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pel%C3%ADcula\">películas</a>&nbsp;realizadas por&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Walt Disney Pictures\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walt_Disney_Pictures\">Disney</a>&nbsp;para&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Televisión\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Televisi%C3%B3n\">televisión</a>.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Por décadas los australianos han sido valorados por los&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Ganadero\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ganadero\">ganaderos</a>&nbsp;debido a su versatilidad inherente y formación. Mientras ellos continúan trabajando como stockdogs y compiten en los ensayos de pastoreo, la raza se ha ganado el reconocimiento en otros papeles debido a su capacidad de entrenamiento y el afán de complacer, y son muy respetados por sus habilidades en la obediencia.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Al igual que todas las razas de trabajo, el australiano tiene mucha energía y dinamismo, y por lo general necesita un trabajo que hacer. A menudo se destaca en los deportes del perro, como la agilidad, flyball y&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Frisbee\" href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frisbee\">frisbee</a>. También son de gran éxito en cuanto búsqueda y rescate, perros de detección, guía, servicio y de terapia. Y, sobre todo, pueden ser compañeros de la familia.</p>','','full_html'),('node','article',0,32,32,'und',0,'<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The&nbsp;<strong>Australian Shepherd</strong>, often known simply as the \"Aussie\", is a medium-sized&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Breed\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breed\">breed</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dog\">dog</a>&nbsp;that was, despite its name, developed on&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Ranch\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranch\">ranches</a>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Western United States\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_United_States\">Western United States</a>, during the 19th century.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">There are different theories regarding the association of the breed with Australia, but there is no consensus on why it was adopted.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>Genetic research has found that Australian Shepherds and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Border Collie\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Border_Collie\">Border Collies</a>&nbsp;are closely related to each other; both are slightly more distantly related to other kinds of&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Collies\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collies\">Collies</a>&nbsp;and to&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Shetland Sheepdog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shetland_Sheepdog\">Shetland Sheepdogs</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Aussies rose in popularity with a boom in&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Western riding\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_riding\">Western riding</a>,<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<em><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Wikipedia:Please clarify\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify\"><span title=\"(January 2017)\">why?</span></a></em>]</sup>&nbsp;after World War II.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup>&nbsp;They became known to the general public through&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Rodeo\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rodeo\">rodeos</a>,&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Horse show\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horse_show\">horse shows</a>, and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"The Walt Disney Company\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Walt_Disney_Company\">Disney</a>&nbsp;movies made for television.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">For many years, Aussies have been valued by stockmen for their versatility and trainability. They have a similar look to the popular&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"English Shepherd\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_Shepherd\">English Shepherd</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Border Collie\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Border_Collie\">Border Collie</a>&nbsp;breeds. While they continue to work as&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Stock dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stock_dog\">stock dogs</a>&nbsp;and compete in&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Herding trial\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herding_trial\">herding trials</a>, the breed has earned recognition in other roles due to their trainability and eagerness to please and are highly regarded for their skills in obedience.<sup id=\"cite_ref-akc.org_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-akc.org-8\">[8]</a></sup>Like all working breeds, the Aussie has considerable energy and drive and usually needs a job to do. It often excels at&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Dog sports\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dog_sports\">dog sports</a>&nbsp;such as&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Dog agility\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dog_agility\">dog agility</a>, and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Disc dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc_dog\">frisbee</a>. They are also highly successful&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Search and rescue dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Search_and_rescue_dog\">search and rescue dogs</a>, disaster dogs,&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Detection dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Detection_dog\">detection dogs</a>,&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Guide dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guide_dog\">guide dogs</a>,&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Service dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Service_dog\">service dogs</a>, and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Therapy dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy_dog\">therapy dogs</a>. They are considered the 17th-most popular dog breed in the United States.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Shepherd#cite_note-9\">[9]</a></sup></p>','','full_html'),('node','article',0,33,33,'und',0,'<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Le&nbsp;<strong>berger belge</strong>&nbsp;est une race de&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Chien de berger\" href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chien_de_berger\">Chien de berger</a>. La&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Nomenclature FCI\" href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nomenclature_FCI\">Nomenclature FCI</a>&nbsp;le classe ainsi&nbsp;:</p><ul style=\"list-style-type: disc; margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1.6em; list-style-image: url(\'data:image/svg+xml,%3C%3Fxml%20version%3D%221.0%22%20encoding%3D%22UTF-8%22%3F%3E%0A%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20version%3D%221.1%22%20width%3D%225%22%20height%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3Ccircle%20cx%3D%222.5%22%20cy%3D%229.5%22%20r%3D%222.5%22%20fill%3D%22%2300528c%22%2F%3E%0A%3C%2Fsvg%3E%0A\'); color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Groupe I - Chiens de berger et de bouvier (sauf chiens de bouvier suisses)</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Section I - Chiens de berger avec épreuve de travail.</li></ul><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Physiquement, le berger belge est un&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Lupoïde\" href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lupo%C3%AFde\">lupoïde</a>&nbsp;de taille moyenne, de construction médioligne qui allie la puissance de son ossature et de sa musculature sèche à l\'élégance générale de ses lignes et à la souplesse de ses allures. C\'est un&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Chien\" href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chien\">chien</a>&nbsp;vif, souvent intelligent. Il brille dans la majorité des disciplines sportives reconnues par la SCC (agilité, obéissance, ring, RCI,&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background: none;\" title=\"Pistage\" href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pistage\">pistage</a>, décombres...) Il est souvent très proche de son maître.</p>','','full_html'),('node','article',0,34,34,'und',0,'<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: #252525; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The&nbsp;<strong>Belgian Shepherd</strong>&nbsp;(also known as the&nbsp;<strong>Belgian Sheepdog</strong>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<strong>Chien de Berger Belge</strong>) is a&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Breed\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breed\">breed</a>&nbsp;of medium-to-large-sized&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Herding dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herding_dog\">herding dog</a>. It originated in Belgium and is similar to other&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Sheep\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sheep\">sheep</a>&nbsp;herding&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dog\">dogs</a>&nbsp;from that region, including the&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Dutch Shepherd\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dutch_Shepherd\">Dutch Shepherd</a>, the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"German Shepherd\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_Shepherd\">German Shepherd</a>, the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Briard\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Briard\">Briard</a>, and others. Four types have been identified by various registries as separate breeds or varieties:&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Groenendael\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Groenendael\">Groenendael</a>,&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Laekenois\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laekenois\">Laekenois</a>,&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Tervuren dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tervuren_dog\">Tervuren</a>, and&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\" title=\"Malinois dog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malinois_dog\">Malinois</a>.</p>','','full_html');
